 "diagnosis": {
  "primary_causes": [
   "handoff_address_resolution_missing",
   "workflow_events_not_delivered_to_downstream_inboxes"
  ],
  "secondary_causes": [
   "misleading_send_chat_denial_message",
   "sales_budget_consumed_by_per_tick_customer_events_and_basis_chores"
  ],
  "excluded_causes": [
   "control_gate_denial (all K-* knobs false; zero submit_application denials)",
   "model_specific_failure (same structural pattern in all four trials, two seeds, R1 and R4)",
   "mutation_side_effect (same pattern in both control arms; circulation gate passed 4/4)"
  ],
  "mechanism": "Turn scheduling is inbox-driven (a seat acts only when its inbox is non-empty). submit_application and request_approval write to the ledger only and enqueue no inbox message, and agents have no directory mapping role names to seat ids, so sales-to-application handoff chat failed 74/74 with role-name addressing. Application-role seats therefore received almost no turns and lifecycle tools beyond a single submission were never attempted."
 },
